<br>
I think I'd make a cross between Pokèmon, Ultima Online, and Final Fantasy.  It'd be a dynamic world with an evolving story much of which would reveal itself through quests.  Graphics would be kinda cartoony/cute and easy on the video cards so you could pile 50 players into a stadium and not have people's computers exploding.<br>
<br>
It'd be 100% skill based (no levels) so you could make whatever kinda character you wanted.  There'd be a skill cap, but skills would be weighted differently depending on how related they were to other skills (ie: A person with Mining, Blacksmithing, and Blunt weapons would use up less against her skill cap than someone with Swordsmanship, Healing, and Fung Shwei).  So you could have a broad based character with fewer skills, or a more focused character with lots.  You could also change your mind that way by just taking up new skills instead and forgetting the old ones (rather than making a new character).<br>
<br>
PvP wouldn't exist on a player -vs- player level, but there'd be a whole monster rancher / Pokèmon / virtual pet kinda aspect to the game too, and you could have your pets challenge other people's pets.  I'd strongly consider not letting players fight at all (not even NPCs) and the pets do all the battling.  Like the pets get combat skills, and the player characters get tradeskill type skills.<br>
<br>
There'd be two types of staff.  Support staff, and event staff.  Support staff would help you with bugs n such.  Event staff would plan fun things for players to do, advance storylines, etc.  They'd be separate people so there wouldn't ever be days when nothing was going on just because support staff was busy.<br>
<br>
Character graphics would be fairly customizable (hair color, eye color, etc).  When you talked to someone, their picture would pop up in a big word bubble kinda thing.  And you could select from a whole bunch of portraits, and color them in with the &quot;fill&quot; tool however you wanted (if you wanted someone with green skin and orange hair, go for it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
Races would probably be only human, or human / fey (pixies, sprites, etc).<br>
<br>
Would try hard to make the game involving and fun right from the start (vs focusing on attaining a certain degree of skill or whatever before the fun starts).  Kinda like how you can pop in Legend of Zelda, and even before you have your boomerang and your 14 heart containers and your magic wand and the game's still fun.<br>
<br>
- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukelisk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelisk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>No, YOU'RE evil<br>Look out! ...Rar! </span><br>  Posts: 491<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/6/02 8:20:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=84.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/CyrusVI/fullsize/keliskpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If you could design your own MMORPG?</span><hr size=1> Your MMORPG sounds a helluva lot like Ragnarok Online.  The graphics used in that game are probably my favorite of any MMORPG I've ever seen-They use high quality SD sprites for characters and mosters, and a 3d rendered environment. neato!  And the chat text comes up above each person in speech bubbles.<br>
